    <note type="dates"><date>1818/19–76</date></note>
    <sex value="M"/>
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Bank manager and naturalist. Employee of the Burton, Uttoxeter, and Ashbourne Union Bank in Burton-upon-Trent, Staffordshire, 1834; manager, 1865. Member of the Entomological Society of London, 1849; fellow of the Geological Society of London and the Royal Geographical Society; member of the Botanical Society of London. A life-long friend and patron of Henry Walter Bates; Bates’s letters to him from the Amazon were published in the <hi rend="italic">Zoologist</hi>, 1849–58.</p></note>
